TSCG dominates LLMLingua-2 on both dimensions: 90.6\% token savings (vs.\ 60.6\%) with 93.3\% accuracy (vs.\ 80.0\%). The compound pipeline (Condition~D) achieves maximal compression but produces output that Claude interprets as corrupted text, indicating that TSCG already removes all structural redundancy---LLMLingua-2's statistical pruning then destroys the remaining semantically critical tokens.

\emph{Note on compression figures:} The 90.6\% savings reported here differ from the 71.7\% reported in \S\ref{sec:domain-benchmarks} because the LLMLingua comparison uses full verbose tool-description prompts (avg.\ 2,009 tokens) that include natural-language parameter descriptions, examples, and usage notes---the format that LLMLingua is designed to compress. The standard benchmark (\S\ref{sec:domain-benchmarks}) uses shorter tool descriptions (avg.\ $\sim$670 tokens) that are already partially concise. Both figures are correct for their respective input formats.
